<p>Paid after dinner. Bathing Parade to Erquinghem Baths Gass alarm test on Parade ground with helmets on &amp; roll call.</p>
<p>8th. Saturday.<br/>Had some of the new bayonet fighting exercises to day by Capt. F. Letterwriting after Parade.</p>
<p>9th Sunday.<br/>Packed up &amp; Paraded 9am ready for marching. Huts cleaned up &amp; left 11am on good roads with lovely weather. Dinner on the roadside about 2pm. &amp; reached our new billets at Caestres 15 miles distance about 6pm. very tired slept in shed alongside windmill ( P.Cards of same sent to K.C.)</p>
<p>10th. Monday.<br/>Up 7am had look through mill which is still used.</p>
